00:54:06.440 --> 00:54:08.920
If you didn't make the most of it, it was up to you.

00:54:08.920 --> 00:54:09.280
Right.

00:54:09.280 --> 00:54:11.480
But do you know, it was taken out of your pay packet

00:54:11.480 --> 00:54:11.880
every week.

00:54:11.880 --> 00:54:12.560
Right.

00:54:12.560 --> 00:54:14.440
Did some people complain about that?

00:54:14.440 --> 00:54:16.080
No, it was up to them.

00:54:16.080 --> 00:54:18.480
You know, if you didn't want to come on the trips,

00:54:18.480 --> 00:54:20.240
if you didn't want to come on the dinner,

00:54:20.240 --> 00:54:22.280
it was you were bad luck.

00:54:22.280 --> 00:54:24.280
But you didn't have an actual building, you know,

00:54:24.280 --> 00:54:26.360
like in Morriston Motors, they had an actual building.

00:54:26.360 --> 00:54:28.920
Oh, no, no, no.

00:54:28.920 --> 00:54:29.600
Nothing like that.

00:54:29.600 --> 00:54:31.880
Did you have any sports teams, any dance teams?

00:54:31.880 --> 00:54:33.440
No, nothing, no.

00:54:33.440 --> 00:54:35.120
Just the enjoyment side of it.

00:54:35.120 --> 00:54:36.000
Yeah.

00:54:36.000 --> 00:54:37.680
And then Shadow Band, is that where it's at?

00:54:37.680 --> 00:54:38.840
Oh, yes.

00:54:38.840 --> 00:54:39.360
We enjoyed.

00:54:39.360 --> 00:54:41.080
Did you have fun on the buses there on the way back?

00:54:41.080 --> 00:54:43.840
We used to go to shows in London, you know.

00:54:43.840 --> 00:54:46.080
Oh, and then shopping trips.

00:54:46.080 --> 00:54:48.760
We even went strawberry picking.

00:54:48.760 --> 00:54:49.960
I've been to Herlyford.

00:54:49.960 --> 00:54:53.280
Oh, see, that's all going now.

00:54:53.280 --> 00:54:55.080
Oh, it's so fun.

00:54:55.080 --> 00:54:56.160
Those were the days.

00:54:56.160 --> 00:54:57.520
Yeah.

00:54:57.520 --> 00:55:00.200
None of it now, not these days.

00:55:00.200 --> 00:55:01.040
Well, do you know what?

00:55:01.040 --> 00:55:04.160
A bus trip these days, you know, like a trip,

00:55:04.160 --> 00:55:06.560
say you're going to see a show, it costs an hour and a leg.

00:55:06.560 --> 00:55:07.240
I know.

00:55:07.240 --> 00:55:09.320
If you want to go and see The Lion King or something,

00:55:09.320 --> 00:55:09.800
it can't.

00:55:09.800 --> 00:55:12.560
Well, we're going to Lion King in London now.

00:55:12.560 --> 00:55:13.640
Are you?

00:55:13.640 --> 00:55:15.520
Well, a moment now.

00:55:15.520 --> 00:55:17.200
Do you want me to tap?

00:55:17.200 --> 00:55:18.000
We're safe now.

00:55:18.000 --> 00:55:21.400
Ha, ha, ha.

00:55:21.400 --> 00:55:23.920
Right, we've talked about music now, haven't we?

00:55:26.920 --> 00:55:30.440
Did the bosses, didn't that mind people chatting on the factory

00:55:30.440 --> 00:55:31.200
floor, did they?

00:55:31.200 --> 00:55:33.000
Well, now and again, you know, they tell you,

00:55:33.000 --> 00:55:34.760
you know, carry on with your work.

00:55:34.760 --> 00:55:35.440
Yeah.

00:55:35.440 --> 00:55:39.240
You couldn't help chatting, but because you were earning

00:55:39.240 --> 00:55:41.920
your own money anyway.

00:55:41.920 --> 00:55:46.880
When I was in Coggy when I started, you earned all what you

00:55:46.880 --> 00:55:49.240
earned, you had, only what you had, you know.

00:55:49.240 --> 00:55:53.120
But when you went to Pains then, you had like a flat rate first,

00:55:53.120 --> 00:55:55.000
and then money on top, you know.

00:55:55.000 --> 00:55:58.040
I can't remember what it was now, so long ago.

00:55:58.040 --> 00:56:01.440
But when we worked in Coggy, saying again about the bosses,

00:56:01.440 --> 00:56:04.680
the girls used to come in and roll us big head scarves

00:56:04.680 --> 00:56:08.320
on their heads because they were going out every night, that's it.

00:56:08.320 --> 00:56:10.320
That was stopped completely when we moved.

00:56:10.320 --> 00:56:10.840
Oh, was it?

00:56:10.840 --> 00:56:11.840
Yeah.

00:56:11.840 --> 00:56:13.920
Mr. Wynod wouldn't allow you to come in and curl us.

00:56:13.920 --> 00:56:14.920
What did he say then?

00:56:14.920 --> 00:56:17.320
Well, then blow dry him then, didn't he?

00:56:17.320 --> 00:56:18.120
But years ago.

00:56:18.120 --> 00:56:20.520
But would he tell the girls, right, don't come in tomorrow?

00:56:20.520 --> 00:56:22.160
Yeah, well, tell the supervisors, see.

00:56:22.160 --> 00:56:22.880
Oh, right.

00:56:22.880 --> 00:56:25.960
And not, you know, that's not allowed kind of thing.

00:56:25.960 --> 00:56:27.800
But they weren't doing any harm, were they?

00:56:27.800 --> 00:56:28.080
No, no.

00:56:28.080 --> 00:56:29.480
He just thought it was wrong.

00:56:29.480 --> 00:56:32.760
Listen, tell you something, I had my ears pierced in the toilet.

00:56:33.360 --> 00:56:34.720
If he knew.

00:56:34.720 --> 00:56:36.720
Oh, my God.

00:56:36.720 --> 00:56:39.720
That's the type of, you know.

00:56:39.720 --> 00:56:40.720
Yeah.

00:56:40.720 --> 00:56:43.720
So what did the girls say when he said no rollers?

00:56:43.720 --> 00:56:45.720
Well, they just accepted it then.

00:56:45.720 --> 00:56:46.720
No, they'll...

00:56:46.720 --> 00:56:48.720
I think that used to happen in a few places.

00:56:48.720 --> 00:56:49.720
Oh, yes.

00:56:49.720 --> 00:56:53.720
The girls come in full head full of rollers, head scarves.

00:56:53.760 --> 00:56:55.720
Did you have to tell anybody, look,

00:56:55.720 --> 00:56:56.720
that you've chatted a bit less?

00:56:56.720 --> 00:56:58.720
Because it's awkward, isn't it?

00:56:58.720 --> 00:57:00.720
Oh, no one would say no at this order

00:57:00.720 --> 00:57:02.720
or to be out at a certain time.

00:57:02.720 --> 00:57:05.720
I'd say, oh, come on, girls, play the game now, no.

00:57:05.720 --> 00:57:08.720
Let's have a little bit less chatting.

00:57:08.720 --> 00:57:11.720
And they would no complaint, they would then, you know.

00:57:11.720 --> 00:57:14.720
And hopefully if there was a rest of the girls,

00:57:14.720 --> 00:57:16.720
they would have said no.

00:57:16.720 --> 00:57:18.720
And then they would have said, no.

00:57:18.720 --> 00:57:20.720
And then they would have said, no.

00:57:20.720 --> 00:57:22.720
And they would then, you know.

00:57:22.720 --> 00:57:24.720
And hopefully if there was a rest of the girls,

00:57:24.720 --> 00:57:28.720
they would stay on, you know, and it was really good.

00:57:28.720 --> 00:57:30.720
So it was Monday to Friday, was it?

00:57:30.720 --> 00:57:31.720
Yes.

00:57:31.720 --> 00:57:32.720
Was there a Saturday and a Saturday?

00:57:32.720 --> 00:57:33.720
Saturday and a Saturday, yes.

00:57:33.720 --> 00:57:34.720
Would you have to do a Saturday?

00:57:34.720 --> 00:57:37.720
No, no, it depends how much work was available

00:57:37.720 --> 00:57:39.720
on where you were, you know.

00:57:39.720 --> 00:57:41.720
As I say, if there was a certain time

00:57:41.720 --> 00:57:43.720
we had to get these orders out,

00:57:43.720 --> 00:57:45.720
the girls would work on in the nights and all.

00:57:45.720 --> 00:57:49.720
No, till six o'clock, up at six in the nights, you know.

00:57:49.720 --> 00:57:51.720
So it was through choice, though, isn't it?

00:57:51.720 --> 00:57:52.720
Yes, oh yes.

00:57:52.720 --> 00:57:55.720
Oh, we'd ask them all, do you mind staying tonight, you know.

00:57:55.720 --> 00:57:57.720
Would that be at the same rate, then?

00:57:57.720 --> 00:57:58.720
Yes, yes.

00:57:58.720 --> 00:57:59.720
No, they'd have time and a half, then.

00:57:59.720 --> 00:58:01.720
They'd have overtime, see.

00:58:01.720 --> 00:58:02.720
Yeah, that's quite good, isn't it?

00:58:02.720 --> 00:58:03.720
Yeah.

00:58:03.720 --> 00:58:04.720
Yeah.

00:58:04.720 --> 00:58:05.720
Oh, there's a question here.

00:58:05.720 --> 00:58:07.720
Were you allowed to smoke while working?

00:58:07.720 --> 00:58:08.720
I don't think so.

00:58:08.720 --> 00:58:09.720
No.

00:58:09.720 --> 00:58:12.720
Only in the smoking base provided.

00:58:12.720 --> 00:58:13.720
Yeah.

00:58:15.720 --> 00:58:18.720
Have you suffered any long,

00:58:18.720 --> 00:58:20.720
I don't think this is applicable to you.

00:58:20.720 --> 00:58:21.720
I'll ask it anyway.

00:58:21.720 --> 00:58:23.720
Have you suffered any long-term effects

00:58:23.720 --> 00:58:25.720
of working in the factory, you know,

00:58:25.720 --> 00:58:27.720
on your health or anything like that?

00:58:27.720 --> 00:58:28.720
Tinnitus, bad.

00:58:28.720 --> 00:58:29.720
I got a hearing aid.

00:58:29.720 --> 00:58:30.720
All right.

00:58:30.720 --> 00:58:32.720
Very bad, because of the noise.

00:58:32.720 --> 00:58:35.720
Because, you know, on the make-up floor,

00:58:35.720 --> 00:58:37.720
which we call linking, seaming and all that,

00:58:37.720 --> 00:58:38.720
the noise wasn't too bad.

00:58:38.720 --> 00:58:39.720
Yeah.

00:58:39.720 --> 00:58:40.720
But because it was on the staff,

00:58:40.720 --> 00:58:42.720
and I had to go on to the knitting floor

00:58:42.720 --> 00:58:45.720
and things like that, the noise over the years

00:58:45.720 --> 00:58:47.720
has affected my ears.

00:58:48.720 --> 00:58:50.720
Could you get any compensation for that?

00:58:50.720 --> 00:58:52.720
Well, not really.

00:58:52.720 --> 00:58:54.720
It's difficult to pull, I suppose.

00:58:54.720 --> 00:58:56.720
You know, my hearing isn't too bad.

00:58:56.720 --> 00:58:58.720
It's just because of the tinnitus, it's so bad.

00:58:58.720 --> 00:59:01.720
I got a hearing aid to mask the ringing

00:59:01.720 --> 00:59:02.720
and things in my head.

00:59:02.720 --> 00:59:03.720
Yeah.

00:59:03.720 --> 00:59:05.720
But that's about the only,

00:59:05.720 --> 00:59:07.720
and I think the strain on your eyes over the years

00:59:07.720 --> 00:59:09.720
goes anyway, you know,

00:59:09.720 --> 00:59:12.720
because of the fluorescent lighting and such fine work.

00:59:12.720 --> 00:59:13.720
Yeah.

00:59:13.720 --> 00:59:14.720
What about your hands?

00:59:14.720 --> 00:59:15.720
Are they stinging?

00:59:15.720 --> 00:59:16.720
Well, I got dramatic anyway.

00:59:16.720 --> 00:59:19.720
I mean, that's common, overage in it, you know.

00:59:19.720 --> 00:59:20.720
Yeah.

00:59:22.720 --> 00:59:25.720
When men started working there,

00:59:25.720 --> 00:59:28.720
I've asked this in a way before,

00:59:28.720 --> 00:59:32.720
when you moved to the factory in Pains,

00:59:32.720 --> 00:59:33.720
did they get teased then?

00:59:33.720 --> 00:59:36.720
Because, you know, there were more men coming in.

00:59:36.720 --> 00:59:37.720
Did they get teased by the good, no-ones?

00:59:37.720 --> 00:59:38.720
Well, to be honest, no.

00:59:38.720 --> 00:59:40.720
No, it was just accepted, you know.

00:59:40.720 --> 00:59:41.720
Yeah.

00:59:41.720 --> 00:59:45.720
Everybody got on with everybody else kind of thing.

00:59:45.720 --> 00:59:47.720
There was never no animosity at all.

00:59:49.720 --> 00:59:51.720
If somebody got married,

00:59:51.720 --> 00:59:53.720
or, you know, say one of the girls was getting married,

00:59:53.720 --> 00:59:56.720
would she get teased, or would there be tricks played on?

00:59:56.720 --> 00:59:58.720
Listen, they used to come in, in the wedding dresses first,

00:59:58.720 --> 01:00:01.720
to see them, if they got married in the week.

01:00:01.720 --> 01:00:03.720
Before or after?

01:00:03.720 --> 01:00:06.720
And then, the line then, every line,

01:00:06.720 --> 01:00:08.720
well, the link in the make-up pro,

01:00:08.720 --> 01:00:11.720
we used to collect 50 pence a week of the girls,

01:00:11.720 --> 01:00:14.720
not 50 pence, whatever it was,

01:00:14.720 --> 01:00:16.720
and the supervisors used to keep it.

01:00:16.720 --> 01:00:18.720
Anybody getting married, have a baby or anything,

01:00:18.720 --> 01:00:21.720
the present would be given out of this money.

01:00:21.720 --> 01:00:23.720
So you had it already, you didn't do a collection of...

01:00:23.720 --> 01:00:25.720
No, we had it already,

01:00:25.720 --> 01:00:27.720
and the money would come out of that then.

01:00:27.720 --> 01:00:30.720
But some of the girls come in, they come out on a Friday,

01:00:30.720 --> 01:00:32.720
they come in in the wedding dress.

01:00:34.720 --> 01:00:36.720
That's how it was lovely.

01:00:37.720 --> 01:00:42.720
And I remember, before Mr Wynlight finished, obviously,

01:00:42.720 --> 01:00:45.720
he was coming to work one morning on T.Crow's flats,

01:00:45.720 --> 01:00:47.720
and he hit a cow on the road.

01:00:49.720 --> 01:00:51.720
Christmas, and I remember, we had the dinner

01:00:51.720 --> 01:00:53.720
at the top of the factory, like I told you,

01:00:53.720 --> 01:00:56.720
two other girls, I had an outfit,

01:00:57.720 --> 01:00:59.720
came out to the canteen,

01:00:59.720 --> 01:01:02.720
and I can't find the photos, I've got photos,

01:01:02.720 --> 01:01:05.720
Meyer and this other girl, in this...

01:01:05.720 --> 01:01:07.720
Well, you should have seen his face,

01:01:07.720 --> 01:01:09.720
but he took it all, in good part,

01:01:09.720 --> 01:01:11.720
and he had a big crack at it.

01:01:11.720 --> 01:01:13.720
I'm the one that got away.

01:01:15.720 --> 01:01:17.720
And he took it all in good part, you know.

01:01:18.720 --> 01:01:20.720
He didn't kill the girl then, did he?

01:01:20.720 --> 01:01:22.720
He must have made a dentist scar.

01:01:26.720 --> 01:01:29.720
We've talked about hours and shift work,

01:01:29.720 --> 01:01:32.720
and girls had to clock in and clock out, does it?

01:01:32.720 --> 01:01:35.720
Yes, yes. Now you had to clock in and out yourself.

01:01:35.720 --> 01:01:37.720
You know, it wasn't accepted for somebody else

01:01:37.720 --> 01:01:39.720
to clock you in if you were late,

01:01:39.720 --> 01:01:41.720
or clock you out if you'd gone early.

01:01:41.720 --> 01:01:43.720
You had to do that yourself, see.

01:01:43.720 --> 01:01:46.720
Were there any penalties for being late then?

01:01:46.720 --> 01:01:48.720
No, you just lost money.

01:01:48.720 --> 01:01:50.720
Because I know in some factories,

01:01:50.720 --> 01:01:52.720
if you were like two minutes late, over two minutes,

01:01:52.720 --> 01:01:54.720
you lost a quarter of an hour or something.

01:01:54.720 --> 01:01:55.720
Oh, no, no.

01:01:55.720 --> 01:01:56.720
It wasn't that.

01:01:56.720 --> 01:01:58.720
No, because it was piecework, see, as well, you know.

01:01:58.720 --> 01:02:01.720
Did any other girls ever try and get somebody else

01:02:01.720 --> 01:02:03.720
to clock in for them?

01:02:03.720 --> 01:02:05.720
Well, if they did, we didn't know about it.

01:02:05.720 --> 01:02:06.720
Oh, right.

01:02:06.720 --> 01:02:08.720
But it's different with piecework anyway, isn't it?

01:02:08.720 --> 01:02:09.720
Yes, yes.

01:02:09.720 --> 01:02:11.720
Because you're going to lose out.

01:02:11.720 --> 01:02:13.720
But you did have a flat rate, see, as well.

01:02:13.720 --> 01:02:16.720
You know, so much an hour you were having on top of your wage.

01:02:16.720 --> 01:02:20.720
Well, then, if you're, you know, the office would count up

01:02:20.720 --> 01:02:22.720
by the end of the week.

01:02:22.720 --> 01:02:24.720
If you'd gone out to the dentist or something,

01:02:24.720 --> 01:02:26.720
you had to clock in and out.

01:02:26.720 --> 01:02:28.720
You know, you were losing those hours, wasn't it?

01:02:28.720 --> 01:02:29.720
Yeah.

01:02:31.720 --> 01:02:34.720
The food in the canteen there, was it OK?

01:02:34.720 --> 01:02:35.720
Lovely.

01:02:35.720 --> 01:02:37.720
What type of thing did they do?

01:02:37.720 --> 01:02:40.720
You had cooked dinners, chips and all that,

01:02:40.720 --> 01:02:44.720
cheaply, because they were subsidised, you know.

01:02:44.720 --> 01:02:48.720
And then, but I never bothered much, to be honest,

01:02:48.720 --> 01:02:51.720
plus they'd have a sweet now and again or something, you know.

01:02:51.720 --> 01:02:53.720
Did you take sandwiches or something?

01:02:53.720 --> 01:02:55.720
Yes, I took sandwiches most of the time.

01:02:55.720 --> 01:02:59.720
Or if I knew there was going to be a beef pie dinner or something,

01:02:59.720 --> 01:03:01.720
perhaps I'd have that.

01:03:01.720 --> 01:03:05.720
Did you ever leave the factory for lunch or did you tend to stay there?

01:03:05.720 --> 01:03:07.720
Oh, I stayed there half an hour, you see.

01:03:07.720 --> 01:03:11.720
Right, yeah, there's not much time to mess around then, is there?

01:03:13.720 --> 01:03:17.720
How many, can you remember how many days holiday a year you had?

01:03:17.720 --> 01:03:21.720
Well, Christmas we'd stop for a fortnight.

01:03:21.720 --> 01:03:26.720
Easter you'd have two days, no more then, you know.

01:03:26.720 --> 01:03:32.720
Two days for, you'd have made it, all the bank holidays,

01:03:32.720 --> 01:03:34.720
but you'd have nothing added on.

01:03:34.720 --> 01:03:35.720
Right.

01:03:35.720 --> 01:03:38.720
You know, summer holidays would have two weeks.

01:03:38.720 --> 01:03:40.720
So was it shut down for the...?

01:03:40.720 --> 01:03:44.720
It was in the beginning, but in the end you could take them when you wanted to.

01:03:44.720 --> 01:03:45.720
Oh, right.

01:03:45.720 --> 01:03:48.720
Well, within, you know, having permission, like, you know.

01:03:48.720 --> 01:03:51.720
Because one line was keeping another line going.

01:03:51.720 --> 01:03:54.720
So that's why they shut down originally,

01:03:54.720 --> 01:03:57.720
because you couldn't afford to have everybody off in the Lincoln,

01:03:57.720 --> 01:03:59.720
there'd be no work for the seamers.

01:03:59.720 --> 01:04:00.720
Yeah.

01:04:00.720 --> 01:04:05.720
Did you, did girls go off on holiday together sometimes?

01:04:05.720 --> 01:04:08.720
You know, were there trips, holiday trips?

01:04:08.720 --> 01:04:09.720
No, I don't think so.

01:04:09.720 --> 01:04:12.720
Where did you go on holiday then when you went?

01:04:12.720 --> 01:04:14.720
When I was working?

01:04:14.720 --> 01:04:15.720
Yes.

01:04:15.720 --> 01:04:18.720
Where we went abroad, my sister and I went abroad, you know.

01:04:18.720 --> 01:04:22.720
Before we went, when my son was small,

01:04:22.720 --> 01:04:25.720
I think he was about five when we started going abroad,

01:04:25.720 --> 01:04:29.720
we'd go to Temby in a caravan, you know.

01:04:29.720 --> 01:04:34.720
My sister now, her in-laws had caravans down in Temby.

01:04:34.720 --> 01:04:35.720
Oh, right.

01:04:35.720 --> 01:04:37.720
And we used to go down there, you know.

01:04:37.720 --> 01:04:38.720
Yeah.

01:04:38.720 --> 01:04:40.720
You enjoyed going on holiday then?

01:04:40.720 --> 01:04:42.720
Yes, loved it.

01:04:42.720 --> 01:04:46.720
So you used to get the bus to work initially.

01:04:46.720 --> 01:04:51.720
Did you buy a car at some point then, or did you carry on with this?

01:04:51.720 --> 01:04:55.720
Yes, we had a car, well, my husband had a car before we got married.

01:04:55.720 --> 01:05:00.720
And because him working then, different shifts and things, you know.

01:05:00.720 --> 01:05:02.720
I didn't drive straight away,

01:05:02.720 --> 01:05:07.720
but then I passed my test two years after we got married.

01:05:07.720 --> 01:05:09.720
One car then, in it.

01:05:09.720 --> 01:05:12.720
Because when you worked in Ford, you had to go to work in a car, you know.

01:05:12.720 --> 01:05:14.720
You had to have a car then.

01:05:14.720 --> 01:05:15.720
Yeah, yeah.

01:05:15.720 --> 01:05:18.720
Where were most of the girls from then who worked?

01:05:18.720 --> 01:05:27.720
Well, Tymbl, Llynellu, Tymbl, Ddewna Ddent, Bryn Amann, Garnent, Glyn Amann, Bedws,

01:05:27.720 --> 01:05:29.720
efo'r we, llan o fie.

01:05:29.720 --> 01:05:31.720
Are you still in contact with a few of them?

01:05:31.720 --> 01:05:36.720
When Rose is my best friend, she worked with me.

01:05:36.720 --> 01:05:38.720
I see her every week.

01:05:38.720 --> 01:05:42.720
My cousin living up here, she worked with me.

01:05:42.720 --> 01:05:47.720
A lot of the girls I don't see for a long, long time, but you never forget, you know.

01:05:47.720 --> 01:05:48.720
No.

01:05:48.720 --> 01:05:50.720
No, I don't see them often.

01:05:50.720 --> 01:05:52.720
People don't socialise as much.

01:05:52.720 --> 01:05:53.720
No.

01:05:53.720 --> 01:05:55.720
You know, nobody sees as much.

01:05:55.720 --> 01:05:57.720
People got their own lives, you know.

01:05:57.720 --> 01:05:58.720
Yes, yeah.

01:05:58.720 --> 01:06:01.720
We've spoken a bit about the social activities.

01:06:01.720 --> 01:06:05.720
Can you tell me a bit more about Christmas time at the factory?

01:06:05.720 --> 01:06:08.720
You were saying that there was an actual party at the factory.

01:06:08.720 --> 01:06:09.720
Yes, yeah.

01:06:09.720 --> 01:06:11.720
Then we'd have, as I say...

01:06:11.720 --> 01:06:14.720
Was this at Alan Payne's, now, is it?

01:06:14.720 --> 01:06:15.720
Yes, oh yes.

01:06:15.720 --> 01:06:22.720
I don't remember much about the other two, but in Payne's, obviously, because I was on staff and we were serving the girls.

01:06:22.720 --> 01:06:25.720
Then we'd have, like...

01:06:25.720 --> 01:06:28.720
Oh, we'd have the raffle.

01:06:28.720 --> 01:06:31.720
Big, big, what do you call it, the raffle after food.

01:06:31.720 --> 01:06:33.720
And they used to do then...

01:06:33.720 --> 01:06:39.720
Where somebody would do a sketch or one of the girls would sing, you know.

01:06:39.720 --> 01:06:41.720
Did you sing?

01:06:41.720 --> 01:06:43.720
Oh God, no, you must be joking.

01:06:43.720 --> 01:06:45.720
He didn't have an apartment then.

01:06:45.720 --> 01:06:47.720
No, no.

01:06:47.720 --> 01:06:49.720
So, you know, we had the main meal and then...

01:06:49.720 --> 01:06:51.720
It was a proper meal, was it?

01:06:51.720 --> 01:06:53.720
Oh yes, took it in there.

01:06:53.720 --> 01:06:56.720
Wow. So where did that come from then?

01:06:56.720 --> 01:06:59.720
The canteen. The girls in the canteen used to cook it.

01:06:59.720 --> 01:07:04.720
Barbara and I used to go in and help to clean the veg the day before, right.

01:07:04.720 --> 01:07:06.720
And then we'd cook there.

01:07:06.720 --> 01:07:12.720
And then they'd have a plate and a silver thing, you know, like a stainless steel plate on top.

01:07:12.720 --> 01:07:17.720
You know, keeping warm in under the counter, like in the oven part.

01:07:17.720 --> 01:07:19.720
You know, heated thing.

01:07:19.720 --> 01:07:22.720
And then we'd just take it out and serve them all.

01:07:22.720 --> 01:07:24.720
Oh, hectic.

01:07:24.720 --> 01:07:26.720
Did it get a bit wild there?

01:07:26.720 --> 01:07:31.720
Oh, it was good, mind you. It was really good. Everybody clapped.

01:07:31.720 --> 01:07:33.720
We used to have a lot of fun.

01:07:33.720 --> 01:07:35.720
Could you have a drink on the day there?

01:07:35.720 --> 01:07:37.720
Oh yes, yes. Fair play to him.

01:07:37.720 --> 01:07:41.720
You know, they were allowed nothing before sitting down when you were on the machinery.

01:07:41.720 --> 01:07:43.720
Not a lot to drink.

01:07:43.720 --> 01:07:46.720
But you were allowed like plus one bottle between six or something like that.

01:07:46.720 --> 01:07:48.720
Did you bring a bottle or...?

01:07:48.720 --> 01:07:51.720
Yes, we brought a bottle of your own in, you know.

01:07:51.720 --> 01:07:53.720
It was good.

01:07:53.720 --> 01:07:55.720
Used to make gatoes then for dessert.

01:07:55.720 --> 01:07:58.720
I love cooking. Used to make these big gatoes.

01:07:58.720 --> 01:08:02.720
And girls on other tables used to bring the trifling or something like that, you know.

01:08:02.720 --> 01:08:06.720
The canteen only did the main wheel, see. The dinner.

01:08:06.720 --> 01:08:10.720
So which day would that be on then? The last working day?

01:08:10.720 --> 01:08:12.720
More often than not, yes.

01:08:12.720 --> 01:08:15.720
So what did you do? Work in the morning? Did you actually work?

01:08:15.720 --> 01:08:18.720
Work in the morning. As much as they would do, yeah.

01:08:18.720 --> 01:08:21.720
With the tinsel round their heads and everything like that.

01:08:21.720 --> 01:08:23.720
It was lovely.

01:08:23.720 --> 01:08:25.720
Did girls decorate where they were going?

01:08:25.720 --> 01:08:28.720
Oh yes, the machines would be like Christmas trees.

01:08:28.720 --> 01:08:31.720
Oh, tinsel and balls hanging and...

01:08:31.720 --> 01:08:33.720
They're lovely.

01:08:33.720 --> 01:08:35.720
And we'd have a children's party then.

01:08:35.720 --> 01:08:37.720
Oh, lovely.

01:08:37.720 --> 01:08:40.720
It's supposed to social with the children of the factory workers, you know.

01:08:40.720 --> 01:08:43.720
And we'd have that then and another boy, men then, Cliff.

01:08:43.720 --> 01:08:46.720
How would you find room to have the party then?

01:08:46.720 --> 01:08:52.720
We'd move all the top end of the factory with boxes where we'd store all the orders, you know.

01:08:52.720 --> 01:08:56.720
Because we were in boxes when we finished now.

01:08:56.720 --> 01:09:00.720
We'd move all those boxes all the way down, get everybody to help.

01:09:00.720 --> 01:09:03.720
Moving the boxes down the bottom end where the machines were.

01:09:03.720 --> 01:09:08.720
Then we'd bring the tables out to the canteen and put them in rows then, like that.

01:09:08.720 --> 01:09:10.720
And that's how we did it.

01:09:10.720 --> 01:09:12.720
Ah, children's party.

01:09:12.720 --> 01:09:15.720
We'd go shopping then for gifts for all the children.

01:09:15.720 --> 01:09:17.720
That would be in the factory as well?

01:09:17.720 --> 01:09:18.720
In the factory.

01:09:18.720 --> 01:09:21.720
And Cliff, then the caretaker, would dress up as Santa.

01:09:21.720 --> 01:09:23.720
Oh, it wouldn't be Mr Wainwright.

01:09:23.720 --> 01:09:25.720
Oh no, Mr Wainwright never dressed up.

01:09:25.720 --> 01:09:27.720
It was Cliff that was always dressed up.

01:09:27.720 --> 01:09:29.720
Oh, it sounds good.

01:09:29.720 --> 01:09:31.720
I feel as if I've missed out now.

01:09:31.720 --> 01:09:33.720
That's good.

01:09:33.720 --> 01:09:36.720
That would be on a Saturday, see, Saturday afternoon.

01:09:38.720 --> 01:09:43.720
Is there any one event that you remember from your work in the factory,

01:09:43.720 --> 01:09:49.720
any one particular date or anybody in particular coming to the factory?

01:09:49.720 --> 01:09:54.720
Well, we had Bill, um, he was a bit of a wimp.

01:09:54.720 --> 01:10:00.720
We had Bill Owen, the one that actually last to the summer wine.

01:10:00.720 --> 01:10:01.720
Oh yes.

01:10:01.720 --> 01:10:04.720
He came there, well obviously Princess Anne.

01:10:04.720 --> 01:10:06.720
And we had somebody.

01:10:06.720 --> 01:10:08.720
Why was Bill Owen there then?

01:10:08.720 --> 01:10:11.720
Well, just asked if he could come and have a look around.

01:10:11.720 --> 01:10:12.720
Gosh.

01:10:12.720 --> 01:10:16.720
None of us knew until he was walking through the factory.

01:10:16.720 --> 01:10:18.720
He wasn't in his old hat and...

01:10:18.720 --> 01:10:20.720
No, no, tidy.

01:10:20.720 --> 01:10:25.720
And we had, well I don't remember, a parliament when we had the third Queen's Award.

01:10:27.720 --> 01:10:30.720
Went from the Senedd came, I can't remember his name.

01:10:30.720 --> 01:10:34.720
He wasn't there long after then, in parliament he came down.

01:10:34.720 --> 01:10:37.720
Could you tell me about the day that Princess Anne came then?

01:10:37.720 --> 01:10:39.720
This was to Alan Payne's now?

01:10:39.720 --> 01:10:41.720
Yes, in Ammerford, yeah.

01:10:41.720 --> 01:10:49.720
Just came down as part of a daily thing, I think, and we were visiting different industries, you know.

01:10:49.720 --> 01:10:51.720
And you spoke to her, didn't you?

01:10:51.720 --> 01:10:53.720
Yes, certainly.

01:10:53.720 --> 01:10:58.720
Anyway, she came by helicopter to a part of in a rugby field.

01:10:58.720 --> 01:11:02.720
And then by car then up to the factory, see.

01:11:02.720 --> 01:11:08.720
High security, all these police, all about the, well they were playing clothes, you know.

01:11:08.720 --> 01:11:13.720
Everybody had to be checked out before she came and things, you know.

01:11:13.720 --> 01:11:16.720
How did they check?

01:11:16.720 --> 01:11:18.720
What do you mean check people out?

01:11:18.720 --> 01:11:23.720
Well, I think the inquirer of the manager, who, you know what I mean, was working and things.

01:11:25.720 --> 01:11:28.720
Well, the manager wrecked us then, Les White.

01:11:28.720 --> 01:11:31.720
And so she was there, tidy.

01:11:31.720 --> 01:11:35.720
She had what's called a plaque on the wall that she'd be in.

01:11:35.720 --> 01:11:39.720
And as I say, we had a mac here outside with finger food.

01:11:39.720 --> 01:11:42.720
Bibir Lloyd, they had made the food.

01:11:42.720 --> 01:11:45.720
And it went well.

01:11:45.720 --> 01:11:47.720
What did she say to you then?

01:11:47.720 --> 01:11:49.720
Just asked how long had I been there.

01:11:49.720 --> 01:11:52.720
Very interested in the garments themselves.

01:11:52.720 --> 01:11:58.720
Then I took her up, walked up to where the press was then.

01:11:58.720 --> 01:12:02.720
And explained to her how we were pressing clothes and things, you know.

01:12:02.720 --> 01:12:06.720
And ten minutes, quarter of an hour like that went.

01:12:06.720 --> 01:12:09.720
And she said, oh thank you very much for showing me around.

01:12:09.720 --> 01:12:11.720
And that was it.

01:12:11.720 --> 01:12:14.720
She went, we went out then, all of us with a mac here.

01:12:15.720 --> 01:12:20.720
We stopped by a number of the girls walking down the floor and had a chat, you know.

01:12:20.720 --> 01:12:21.720
Spoke to them.

01:12:21.720 --> 01:12:23.720
So it was really nice.

01:12:23.720 --> 01:12:26.720
What did the girls think then that she'd come to the factory?

01:12:26.720 --> 01:12:31.720
Some girls accepted it, others thought, what a waste of time, you know.

01:12:31.720 --> 01:12:33.720
You get all sorts, don't you?

01:12:33.720 --> 01:12:35.720
Did they have to carry on working that then?

01:12:35.720 --> 01:12:36.720
Yes, yes.

01:12:36.720 --> 01:12:40.720
I suppose that's the whole point of coming to the factory, isn't it?

01:12:40.720 --> 01:12:44.720
I used to have school children down there to be shown around, you know.

01:12:44.720 --> 01:12:46.720
They used to ask you little questions, you know.

01:12:46.720 --> 01:12:48.720
It was lovely.

01:12:48.720 --> 01:12:50.720
It was very much part of the community then, maybe.

01:12:50.720 --> 01:12:51.720
Yes, yes.

01:12:51.720 --> 01:12:55.720
My granddaughter, the youngest, never heard anything about it.

01:12:55.720 --> 01:12:58.720
I said, hello, don't tell me she worked in paints.

01:12:58.720 --> 01:13:01.720
I think all of Emma puts work in paints.

01:13:01.720 --> 01:13:03.720
I think they have.

01:13:06.720 --> 01:13:09.720
So can you tell me there was a shop there as well, wasn't there?

01:13:09.720 --> 01:13:10.720
Yes.

01:13:10.720 --> 01:13:12.720
So that was selling the range of garments?

01:13:12.720 --> 01:13:17.720
Yes, as cut down prices to what you would buy in Harrods and all that, you know.

01:13:17.720 --> 01:13:19.720
Because the garments were top quality.

01:13:19.720 --> 01:13:22.720
Oh yes, cashmere, camelaire, all those.

01:13:22.720 --> 01:13:23.720
Lovely.

01:13:23.720 --> 01:13:25.720
I'll show them, I'll show you them.

01:13:25.720 --> 01:13:26.720
Yeah, a minute.

01:13:26.720 --> 01:13:30.720
We'll finish this first now, because I know where that you need to go at a certain time.

01:13:30.720 --> 01:13:31.720
Oh yes, yeah.

01:13:31.720 --> 01:13:36.720
Perhaps we can take a photo of them after we've finished, that'll be good.

01:13:36.720 --> 01:13:39.720
Right, we're nearly done now, Pat, right?

01:13:39.720 --> 01:13:45.720
So I know the answer to this, but I'm going to ask you anyway, did you enjoy working at the factory?

01:13:45.720 --> 01:13:48.720
Very much, until we went into receivership.

01:13:48.720 --> 01:13:50.720
It was never the same then.

01:13:50.720 --> 01:13:52.720
And that was at the beginning of the nineties?

01:13:52.720 --> 01:13:53.720
Ninety-three.

01:13:53.720 --> 01:13:54.720
Yeah, 1993.

01:13:54.720 --> 01:13:58.720
So what did you enjoy about it?

01:13:58.720 --> 01:14:02.720
Was it the social side, was it the work itself, was it rewarding?

01:14:02.720 --> 01:14:04.720
To be honest, everything.

01:14:04.720 --> 01:14:10.720
I was so involved in things there as well, I was never bored, you know.

01:14:10.720 --> 01:14:15.720
Never went into work and thought, oh god, I've had the time, you know, for me to go home.

01:14:15.720 --> 01:14:17.720
You weren't watching the clock?

01:14:17.720 --> 01:14:18.720
No, not in the beginning.

01:14:18.720 --> 01:14:20.720
No, well, not for years and years.

01:14:20.720 --> 01:14:27.720
But of course, in the end then, when things got new owners and all this, things changed so much, you know.

01:14:27.720 --> 01:14:29.720
In what way? The atmosphere changed?

01:14:29.720 --> 01:14:30.720
Yes, oh yes, yeah.

01:14:30.720 --> 01:14:34.720
No sports and social for interest, you know, nothing like that.

01:14:34.720 --> 01:14:39.720
We didn't have get-togethers anymore and it was just different.

01:14:39.720 --> 01:14:41.720
They weren't very worker friendly then?

01:14:41.720 --> 01:14:42.720
No, no, no.

01:14:42.720 --> 01:14:44.720
Who were the company that took over?

01:14:44.720 --> 01:14:46.720
I don't remember the name of them, no.

01:14:51.720 --> 01:14:53.720
So how long were you there altogether?

01:14:53.720 --> 01:14:55.720
Well, I started in 1962.

01:14:55.720 --> 01:15:01.720
Finished in 1968 to have my son.

01:15:01.720 --> 01:15:06.720
Worked at home then and I went back in 1973.

01:15:06.720 --> 01:15:10.720
And I was there then until they closed in 1998.

01:15:10.720 --> 01:15:13.720
So about 33, 34 years altogether.

01:15:13.720 --> 01:15:16.720
Yeah, for a long time.

01:15:16.720 --> 01:15:18.720
So you saw a lot during that time.

01:15:18.720 --> 01:15:19.720
Part of my life, yeah.

01:15:19.720 --> 01:15:20.720
Yeah, yeah.

01:15:20.720 --> 01:15:25.720
So could you tell me about when you left then?

01:15:25.720 --> 01:15:28.720
There was the receivership in 1993, wasn't there?

01:15:28.720 --> 01:15:29.720
Yeah.

01:15:29.720 --> 01:15:30.720
And then, well, how did that happen?

01:15:30.720 --> 01:15:31.720
We started back in 1994.

01:15:31.720 --> 01:15:32.720
Yeah.

01:15:32.720 --> 01:15:40.720
As I say, the three, Colin Patterson, Les White and James Hinton, were the manager directors then.

01:15:40.720 --> 01:15:42.720
They bought into it.

01:15:42.720 --> 01:15:45.720
They ran it for a few years, but it just didn't work out.

01:15:45.720 --> 01:15:49.720
So this other company up Midlands took over.

01:15:49.720 --> 01:15:53.720
And well, they were.

01:15:53.720 --> 01:16:02.720
In the August then of 1998, I went in to have an operation on my shoulder caused by working there, really, you know, lifting and everything.

01:16:02.720 --> 01:16:16.720
And they closed in the October, but the wearers and the shop were kept on until about the following March because they had to get into the stock and things, you know.

01:16:16.720 --> 01:16:20.720
But everything was moved up to the Midlands.

01:16:20.720 --> 01:16:23.720
And how did you feel that it was all coming to an end?

01:16:23.720 --> 01:16:27.720
Well, to be honest with you, I could see it coming.

01:16:27.720 --> 01:16:30.720
And I think everybody felt the same.

01:16:30.720 --> 01:16:32.720
Nobody was happy there anymore.

01:16:32.720 --> 01:16:34.720
You had this atmosphere, you know.

01:16:34.720 --> 01:16:39.720
But anyway, it was money in the pocket in the end, wasn't it?

01:16:39.720 --> 01:16:42.720
So did you carry on working after that or did you finish?

01:16:42.720 --> 01:16:44.720
No, I finished then.

01:16:44.720 --> 01:16:48.720
And what about the other girls then? How did they feel that it came to an end?

01:16:48.720 --> 01:16:49.720
Well, a lot was sad.

01:16:49.720 --> 01:16:57.720
In a way, it's been good for some of the girls because they've gone on to be carers and things like that, you know.

01:16:57.720 --> 01:17:02.720
I don't know, just sad at the time.

01:17:02.720 --> 01:17:04.720
Yeah, it's sad not to see your friends.

01:17:04.720 --> 01:17:06.720
Because you've got to look for something else from now, you know.

01:17:06.720 --> 01:17:08.720
Yeah.

01:17:08.720 --> 01:17:12.720
I've asked you this already about you being in contact.

01:17:12.720 --> 01:17:19.720
If you had to sum up your time then in the factory, how would you describe it in a few words?

01:17:19.720 --> 01:17:21.720
Happy.

01:17:27.720 --> 01:17:31.720
I think I learnt a lot.

01:17:31.720 --> 01:17:35.720
You learn social skills because you're handling people.

01:17:35.720 --> 01:17:41.720
Being involved with different people, different girls.

01:17:41.720 --> 01:17:47.720
Some had problems that you helped to solve out that made you feel nice because you were helping people.

01:17:47.720 --> 01:17:52.720
Yes, on the whole, I'd say it was a nice time of my life.

01:17:52.720 --> 01:17:56.720
If you hadn't worked there then, where do you think you would have worked?

01:17:56.720 --> 01:18:00.720
I've no idea. I don't know where I'd have ended up.

01:18:00.720 --> 01:18:01.720
Who knows?

01:18:01.720 --> 01:18:02.720
No, who knows?

01:18:02.720 --> 01:18:07.720
I'm just going to pause here. I'll just ask you about the photographs, right, if that's okay?

01:18:07.720 --> 01:18:09.720
Yeah.

